Intriguing Idea: read one page per day for one year and you will be up-to-date on a liftime of teachings from the man widely considered to be "the founder of modern management."

To condense 39 books into one book, and then to summarize that one book is a challenge beyond my capabilities. So, I'll summarize one day instead.

<b>November 12 | The Work of a Manager</b>

~ Managers set objectives
~ Managers organize
~ Managers motivate and communicate
~ Managers establish yardsticks
~ Managers develop people, including themselves

If your team does not grade you highly in each area, then you have some work to do the become a better manager.

This is a book of sound bites. Think of it as a movie trailer. It's designed to tease you and pique your curiosity to learn more. It ranks as #9 on one list of <a href="https://theartofliving.com/best-peter-drucker-books/" target="_blank"><b>The Best Peter Drucker Books of All Time<b>.</a>

To receive the full experience of the teachings of Peter Drucker, consider reading the following:

#2 <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/133700367" target="_blank">The Effective Executive</a>
#3 <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/34522806" target="_blank">Management</a>
#7 <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/736533766" target="_blank">The Essential Drucker</a>

"If there is any one 'secret' of effectiveness, it is concentration. Effective executives do first things first and they do one thing at a time." ~ Peter Drucker
